  "prompt": "Who is Shahrukh Khan?",
  "response": "Shah Rukh Khan, often referred to as SRK, is an Indian actor, film producer, and television personality who is one of the most prominent and influential figures in the Indian film industry, commonly known as Bollywood. Born on November 2, 1965, in New Delhi, India, he gained fame in the late 1980s and has since appeared in over 80 films. \n\nShah Rukh Khan is well-known for his romantic roles in films such as \"Dilwale Dulhania Le Jayenge,\" \"Kabhi Khushi Kabhie Gham,\" \"Dil Se,\" and \"My Name is Khan,\" among many others. He has won numerous awards for his performances, including multiple Filmfare Awards, and is often referred to as the \"King of Bollywood\" or \"Romance King.\"\n\nIn addition to acting, Khan is also a successful film producer and co-owns the production company Red Chillies Entertainment. He is a co-owner of the Kolkata Knight Riders, a franchise cricket team that plays in the Indian Premier League (IPL).\n\nBeyond his work in film, Shah Rukh Khan is known for his philanthropic efforts, involvement in various charitable causes, and has a significant fan following both in India and around the world. He is recognized for his contribution to cinema and has received various honors, including the Padma Shri, one of India's highest civilian awards.",
